Privacy Policy
Download privacy policy
Thank you for visiting maestropizza.com. At Daily Food Co (Maestro Pizza), we deeply value the trust you place in us and are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information when you visit our website.
Your Privacy Commitment
Daily Food Co (Maestro Pizza) is dedicated to protecting your personal information and ensuring a secure online experience. We appreciate your trust and want you to feel confident using our website and services.
Information We Collect and How We Use It
We collect personal information such as names, addresses, email addresses, phone numbers, and location data when you voluntarily provide it. This information is used to:
Process and manage your orders.
Send invoices for online payments.
Customize promotional offers and communications.
Enable accurate delivery of orders to your saved locations.
Types of Information Collected
Customer Phone Numbers: Used to allow you to place and track orders.
Email Addresses: Utilized for sending order invoices and personalized promotions.
Location Data: Required to deliver orders accurately to your saved locations. You can enable location services to improve delivery accuracy.
Payment Information: We use certified online payment gateways to process payments. Payment card details are not stored by Daily Food Co (Maestro Pizza). Instead, we use secure tokens saved on your device to simplify future transactions.
Sharing of Personal Information
We may share personal information such as names, addresses, email addresses, phone numbers, and location data when you voluntarily provide it within the Daily Food Co (Maestro Pizza) Family, which includes our parent company, subsidiaries, and affiliates. Any such use of your information will be in line with this privacy policy.
Occasionally, with your consent, we may send marketing information on behalf of our business partners. We do not share your personal information with these partners; rather, we handle the communication directly.
Third-Party Service Providers
We may employ third-party companies to assist with various functions such as order fulfillment, promotions, and technical support. These providers have access to your personal information only as necessary to perform their functions and are required to use it solely for those purposes.
Cookies
Our website uses cookies to enhance your experience, including remembering you during future visits, managing your shopping cart, and personalizing your web experience. You can adjust your browser settings to manage or disable cookies. Note that disabling cookies may affect site functionality.
Links to Other Sites
Our website may contain links to third-party sites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these sites. Please review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.
Data Retention and Security
We retain your personal information as needed to provide services and fulfill orders. We implement physical, electronic, and managerial safeguards to protect your data. However, no transmission over the internet can be guaranteed as completely secure. By using our site, you acknowledge this risk.
Policy Updates
This Privacy Policy is effective as of Sept 16, 2024. We may update this policy from time to time, and we encourage you to review it periodically for any changes. Any updates will not retroactively affect previously collected information.
What are your Individual Rights?
Under the PDPL the individual who the Personal Data refers to has rights. Whilst these rights are not absolute, they are intended for the protection of an individual’s Personal Data. The rights are as follows:
Right to be informed
The right to know why their Personal Data is being collected, under what legal basis this is done and what their data will be used for
Right to access and request a copy You have the right to access your Personal Data held by Maestro Pizza and request a copy.
Right to delete
Right to rectification
The right to request erasure of the Personal Data that is held about you, under certain conditions.
Right to withdraw consent
The right to withdraw their consent for Processing their Personal Data at any time. To withdraw consent, you can do so through the Maestro Pizza application by navigating to: Profile & Settings > Notification.
How do you Contact us?
If you have any questions or wish to contact us about the contents of this Privacy Notice in the first instance, please contact us through:
DPP@dailyfoodsa.com
Please enable JavaScript to continue using this application.
